div.div:
InterestRate
1. Interest on savings accounts is added to the account annually at the rate of specified interestRate per year. That means that if I have 1M in a savings account with a 0.01 interest rate, 1% of 1 Million is added to my account after 1 year. When a savings account balance is accessed, you must determine if it has been 1 year or more since either the account was created or since interest was added to the account, and add the appropriate interest to the balance if necessary.
2. Interest on credit cards is added to the balance monthly. If you have a 12% interest rate (0.12) then 1% interest will be added to the account monthly. When the balance of a credit card is accessed, check to determine if it has been 1 month or more since the account was created or since interested was added, and if so, add the appropriate interest to the balance.

Requirements
1. The system must have 4 types of accounts: StudentChecking, Checking, Savings, and CreditCard
2. The system must have 3 types of Users: Admins and AccountHolders.
3. Admins can create new accounts. When creating a new account they can create Checking, Savings, or CreditCard Accounts.
4. Interest and Fees should be applied appropriately.
5. Account Access.

Third-Party Users
1. There must be a way for third-party users to receive and send money to other accounts.
2. Third-party users must be added to the database by an admin.
3. In order to receive and send money, Third-Party Users must provide:
a. Their hashed key in the header of the HTTP request.
b. They also must provide the amount.
c. The Account id.
d. The account secret key.
